Russia to Spend Additional $540 Million on Agriculture This Year

-- B y   E k a t e r i n a   S h a t a l o v a
-- 
2011-04-06T10:58:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/russia-to-spend-additional-540-million-on-agriculture-this-year.html
Russia will spend 15.2 billion
rubles ($540 million) more than originally planned to support
agriculture this year, Finance Minister Alexei Kudrin told the
State Duma, or lower chamber of the parliament.  The biggest allocation, about 10 billion rubles, will
support the meat and milk industries, while 3.7 billion rubles
will be used to help farmers lease equipment and with a land
registration program.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  